<item>
            <title>[CSV-75] ExtendedBufferReader does not handle EOL consistently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CSV-75</link>
                <project id="12313222" key="CSV">Commons CSV</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ExtendedBufferReader checks for &apos;\n&apos; (LF) in the read() methods, incrementing linecount when found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the readLine() method calls BufferedReader.readLine() which treats CR, LF and CRLF equally (and drops them).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the code is to be flexible in what it accepts, the class should also allow for CR alone as a line terminator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should work if the code increments the line counter for CR, and for LF if the previous character was not CR.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
