                            <comment id="13239052" author="ebourg" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 00:24:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a test demonstrating the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wonder if the line counting should be handled by the lexer instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239072" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 00:37:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, perhaps it should be done by the lexer. But the quickest fix would be to patch the reader.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wonder whether ExtendedBufferReader is actually necessary; lookAhead() could easily be provided by the Lexer class.&lt;br/&gt;
And I&apos;m not sure that readAgain() is really necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239084" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 00:51:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Enabled new test and added patch to fix it.&lt;br/&gt;
But we should still consider if ExtendedBufferReader is really necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
